Key Match Events: Travis Head scored a crucial 62 off 48 balls, breaking a 95-run partnership between David Miller and Heinrich Klaasen.
Travis Head dismissed Heinrich Klaasen with a straight delivery, followed by Marco Jansen and Gerald Coetzee.
Mitchell Starc and Josh Hazlewood tore through the South African top order, claiming 2-12 and 3-34 respectively from their respective 8 and 10 overs.
David Miller made a vital century off 99 balls, saving South Africa from an embarrassing total of 212.
Australia needed 39 runs with four wickets in hand to win, with Josh Inglis and Pat Cummins guiding the team to a narrow victory.
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head was named player of the match for his exceptional performance with both bat and ball.
Pat Cummins expressed satisfaction with the victory, praising the entire team's efforts and acknowledging the pressure of being in a final.
Tevemba Bavuma, the South African captain, was visibly disappointed with the loss, attributing it to a poor start and the team's inability to get a competitive total.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Travis Head's 62 off 48 balls was crucial in breaking the back of the chase.
Josh Hazlewood's economical figures of 2-12 marked the most economical figures of any Australian bowling eight overs or more since Nathan Bracken in 2006.
South Africa's initial collapse saw them lose four wickets for 24 runs, setting the stage for a tough chase.
